Rain covers are seen on the pitch as rain has delayed start of play of the fourth day of the second Test cricket match between South Africa and India. AFP/Phill Magakoe JOHANNESBURG - Umpires at the Wanderers have decided it's safe enough to resume play on day four of the second test between the Proteas and India. South Africa are chasing 240 for victory and hope to square the series ahead of the third match in Cape Town. Opener Dean Elgar and Rassie van der Dussen took stumps on Wednesday, with the total on 118 for 2 still needing a further 122 for victory. 